pageTitle: Fort Scott Rock Creek Lake / Region 5 / Fishing Locations - Public Waters / Where to Fish in Kansas / Fishing / KDWPT - KDWPT
textBeforeTable: Creel Length/Limits This lake is enrolled into the Community Fisheries Assistance Program. A city fishing permit is no longer required. Water levels are relatively constant. However the City may lower this lake for water supply. This lake supports great shoreline accessability. There is a fish feeder at the primary access area. Crappie, channel catfish and carp can be easily caught at this lake. Don George,KDWP&T Fisheries Biologist 1 mile S, 2 1/2 mile W of Ft.
